Deploy a Container Web App on Amazon EKS using CDK8S

https://aws.amazon.com/tutorials/deploy-webapp-eks/


======================================================================
STEP-1: Create a Cluster (10 mins): This section outlines how to create EKS cluster using CDK. However we going to use Terraform to create EKS cluster

terraform init
terraform plan
terraform apply
terraform destroy

======================================================================
STEP-2: Installing the AWS CDK8S CLI (5 mins)

npm install -g cdk8s-cli

pip3 install pipenv

cd ~/GitHub/aws/eks
mkdir cdk8s
cd cdk8s
cdk8s init python-app


The CDK8s will create following files and folders structure:
├── Pipfile
├── Pipfile.lock
├── cdk8s.yaml
├── dist
│   └── cdk8s.k8s.yaml
├── help
├── imports
│   └── k8s
│       ├── __init__.py
│       ├── _jsii
│       │   ├── __init__.py
│       │   └── k8s@0.0.0.jsii.tgz
│       └── py.typed
└── main.py




Creating service and deployment (5 mins): Launch your application using AWS CDK and AWS CDK8S.
Deploy infrastructure with CDK (10 mins): Learn how to launch your infrastructure using CDK and deploy your application.
Clean Up Resources: In this last part of the guide you learn how to clean after you are done.


